952
1:4:4,424 --> 1:4:6,51
Yeah, maybe,


953
1:4:6,51 --> 1:4:8,929
but l'm going over
to them stockades.


954
1:4:8,929 --> 1:4:10,847
Tell them MPs what l know.


955
1:4:10,847 --> 1:4:13,225
C.J. was in here all evening.


956
1:4:13,225 --> 1:4:15,56
l'm gonna go with you.


957
1:4:15,56 --> 1:4:18,688
Y'all wait up. l'm coming too.


958
1:4:18,688 --> 1:4:20,398
[DOOR SLAMS]


959
1:4:20,398 --> 1:4:23,36
Was Wilkie the only person
out of his bunk?


960
1:4:23,36 --> 1:4:26,863
l guess.
Wilkie came in with the sarge.


961
1:4:26,863 --> 1:4:28,532
But it's hard to say.


962
1:4:28,532 --> 1:4:35,914
lt's been a while and like l said,
l was a little juiced that night.


963
1:4:35,914 --> 1:4:39,417
Ellis.
Yes? Yes, sir?


964
1:4:39,417 --> 1:4:43,463
Find out what's holding up
my investigation of
Wilcox and Byrd.


965
1:4:43,463 --> 1:4:48,677
Yes, sir.


966
1:4:48,677 --> 1:4:51,805
The night Sergeant Waters
was killed, where were you?


967
1:4:51,805 --> 1:4:53,598
l was in the barracks.


968
1:4:53,598 --> 1:5:1,982
l played checkers with Cobb
till 9:30 and then l went to bed.


969
1:5:1,982 --> 1:5:6,319
ls there gonna be
anything else, sir?


970
1:5:6,319 --> 1:5:17,998
Dismissed, private.


971
1:5:17,998 --> 1:5:25,964
[WHlRRlNG]


972
1:5:25,964 --> 1:5:27,424
Let her go.


973
1:5:27,424 --> 1:5:30,844
Let me know when it's full board.
Here we go. Let's go, baby.


974
1:5:30,844 --> 1:5:33,847
MAN 1 : Pick it up.
MAN 2: Keep your rifles up.


975
1:5:33,847 --> 1:5:35,56
[SOLDlERS GRUNT]


976
1:5:35,56 --> 1:5:36,433
That's it.


977
1:5:36,433 --> 1:5:40,145
[BLOWlNG WHlSTLE]


978
1:5:40,145 --> 1:5:42,355
That's it, move out! Move out!
Move your ass!


979
1:5:42,355 --> 1:5:43,857
[SOLDlERS YELLlNG]


980
1:5:43,857 --> 1:5:47,11
That's it, move out!
Move out!


981
1:5:47,11 --> 1:5:51,448
[MAN 2 SHOUTlNG
lNDlSTlNCTLY]


982
1:5:51,448 --> 1:5:56,36
Goddamn it, get going!
That's it, that's it, move it out!


983
1:5:56,36 --> 1:5:58,747
[YELLS THEN GRUNTS]


984
1:5:58,747 --> 1:6:1,291
MAN 2:
Shake it out! Hit that wall!
Get your feet up!


985
1:6:1,291 --> 1:6:3,543
Hurry it up! Hurry it up!


986
1:6:3,543 --> 1:6:6,921
Move out! Move out! That's it!


987
1:6:6,921 --> 1:6:8,34
[MAN 3 SPEAKS lNDlSTlNCTLY]


988
1:6:8,34 --> 1:6:10,592
MAN 3: Watch it!
MAN 2: Shake your ass! That's it!


989
1:6:10,592 --> 1:6:13,762
Move it out!


990
1:6:13,762 --> 1:6:15,764
[GUNSHOTS]


991
1:6:15,764 --> 1:6:17,474
MAN 4:
Move it! Let's go!


992
1:6:17,474 --> 1:6:18,933
[BLOWlNG WHlSTLE]


993
1:6:18,933 --> 1:6:20,685
Ellis!


994
1:6:20,685 --> 1:6:22,479
[SOLDlERS YELLlNG]


995
1:6:22,479 --> 1:6:25,607
Ellis!


996
1:6:25,607 --> 1:6:26,816
[SOLDlER YELLlNG]


997
1:6:26,816 --> 1:6:29,235
[GASPS]


998
1:6:29,235 --> 1:6:31,279
MAN 5:
Hold it!


999
1:6:31,279 --> 1:6:43,708
MAN 6:
Stop shooting!
Stop shooting!


1000
1:6:43,708 --> 1:6:49,547
[WHlRRlNG STOPS]


1001
1:6:49,547 --> 1:6:57,681
Which one of you idiots
is Cobb?


1002
1:6:57,681 --> 1:6:59,808
That's me, sir.


1003
1:6:59,808 --> 1:7:3,103
You all right, captain?


1004
1:7:3,103 --> 1:7:5,23
l wanna talk to you.


1005
1:7:5,23 --> 1:7:8,65
What'd he want
old Cobb for?


1006
1:7:8,65 --> 1:7:10,318
l don't know.


1007
1:7:10,318 --> 1:7:12,404
What'd he ask you,
Pete?


1008
1:7:12,404 --> 1:7:16,157
He just asked a couple
of questions about
the baseball game,


1009
1:7:16,157 --> 1:7:17,742
some about the sarge.


1010
1:7:17,742 --> 1:7:19,536
Didn't amount to too much.


1011
1:7:19,536 --> 1:7:22,706
Yeah, we was
homeys, me and C.J.,
both from Mississippi.


1012
1:7:22,706 --> 1:7:23,998
C.J., from Carmella.


1013
1:7:23,998 --> 1:7:27,794
Me, l'm from up
around Jutlerville,
what they call Snake County.


1014
1:7:27,794 --> 1:7:30,714
How did you feel
when your best friend
was arrested?


1015
1:7:30,714 --> 1:7:33,216
l hated Waters for it, sir.
Hated?


1016
1:7:33,216 --> 1:7:35,885
C.J. ain't killed nobody.


1017
1:7:35,885 --> 1:7:39,472
He hit Waters, didn't he?
Yeah, but the sergeant made him, sir.


1018
1:7:39,472 --> 1:7:42,726
He called that boy things
he ain't never heard before.


1019
1:7:42,726 --> 1:7:46,146
C.J. was from the farm,
a country boy.


1020
1:7:46,146 --> 1:7:50,233
That jail cell started doing
crazy things to C.J., sir.


1021
1:7:50,233 --> 1:7:52,819
lt started closing in on him.


1022
1:7:52,819 --> 1:7:55,28
[KEYS JlNGLlNG]


1023
1:7:55,28 --> 1:8:8,334
[LOCK CLlCKS]


1024
1:8:8,334 --> 1:8:13,84
Are you all right?


1025
1:8:13,84 --> 1:8:19,679
lt's hard to breathe
in these little spaces, Cobb.


1026
1:8:19,679 --> 1:8:24,893
What they doing to you
in here, C.J.?


1027
1:8:24,893 --> 1:8:29,564
Man wasn't made
for this here.


1028
1:8:29,564 --> 1:8:33,86
Nothing was.


1029
1:8:33,86 --> 1:8:37,322
Don't think l'll ever see
an animal in a cage again


1030
1:8:37,322 --> 1:8:40,33
and not feel sorry for it.


1031
1:8:40,33 --> 1:8:41,951
Rather be on a chain gang.


1032
1:8:41,951 --> 1:8:44,788
Oh, come on, homey.


1033
1:8:44,788 --> 1:8:48,166
Don't think l'm getting
out of here, Cobb.


1034
1:8:48,166 --> 1:8:51,2
Feel like l'm going crazy.


1035
1:8:51,2 --> 1:8:53,87
Can't walk in here.


1036
1:8:53,87 --> 1:8:55,507
Can't see the sun.


1037
1:8:55,507 --> 1:9:0,512
l tried to sing,
but nothing won't come out.


1038
1:9:0,512 --> 1:9:6,726
Yesterday, l broke a guitar string.


1039
1:9:6,726 --> 1:9:9,979
[WHlSPERS]
And l lost my dust.


1040
1:9:9,979 --> 1:9:12,357
Got no protection, Cobb.


1041
1:9:12,357 --> 1:9:15,985
[lN NORMAL VOlCE]
Nothing to keep the dogs
from tearing at my bones.


1042
1:9:15,985 --> 1:9:22,45
C.J., stop talking crazy.


1043
1:9:22,45 --> 1:9:29,332
You know who come up here
last night?


1044
1:9:29,332 --> 1:9:38,91
[WHlSPERS]
Sergeant Waters.


1045
1:9:38,91 --> 1:9:44,13
They talking about
giving you five years.


1046
1:9:44,13 --> 1:9:48,101
They call what you did
mutiny, boy.


1047
1:9:48,101 --> 1:9:50,395
That gun ain't mine.


1048
1:9:50,395 --> 1:9:53,189
We know that, C.J.


1049
1:9:53,189 --> 1:9:56,442
We changed the charge
on you this morning.


1050
1:9:56,442 --> 1:10:1,739
You're in here for striking
a superior officer, boy.


1051
1:10:1,739 --> 1:10:4,868
And everybody seen it too.


1052
1:10:4,868 --> 1:10:7,912
Why are you doing this to me,
sarge?


1053
1:10:7,912 --> 1:10:11,82
Oh, don't feel too bad, C.J.


1054
1:10:11,82 --> 1:10:14,878
lt has to be this way.


1055
1:10:14,878 --> 1:10:17,839
You see,


1056
1:10:17,839 --> 1:10:21,467
the first war didn't change
nothing for the Negro.


1057
1:10:21,467 --> 1:10:26,598
But this one,
gonna change everything.


1058
1:10:26,598 --> 1:10:29,559
Them Nazis ain't all crazy.


1059
1:10:29,559 --> 1:10:34,856
Whole lot of people
just can't seem to fit in to
where things seem to be going.


1060
1:10:34,856 --> 1:10:37,525
Like you, C.J.


1061
1:10:37,525 --> 1:10:43,31
See, the black race
can't afford you no more.


1062
1:10:43,31 --> 1:10:46,284
Oh, there used to be a time
we'd see somebody like you


1063
1:10:46,284 --> 1:10:49,454
singing, clowning,
"yes, sir, boss"ing,


1064
1:10:49,454 --> 1:10:51,706
and we wouldn't do anything.


1065
1:10:51,706 --> 1:10:54,0
Folks liked that.


1066
1:10:54,0 --> 1:10:55,668
You were good.


1067
1:10:55,668 --> 1:10:58,421
Homey kind of nigger.


1068
1:10:58,421 --> 1:11:1,883
When they needed somebody
to mistreat, call a name or two,


1069
1:11:1,883 --> 1:11:4,51
they paraded you.


1070
1:11:4,51 --> 1:11:7,931
Reminded them
of the good old days.


1071
1:11:7,931 --> 1:11:11,476
[♪♪♪]


1072
1:11:11,476 --> 1:11:14,771
Not no more.


1073
1:11:14,771 --> 1:11:18,399
The day of the Geechee
is gone, boy.


1074
1:11:18,399 --> 1:11:20,735
And you're going with it.


1075
1:11:20,735 --> 1:11:33,39
We can't let nobody
go on believing
we're all fools like you.


1076
1:11:33,39 --> 1:11:36,96
l waited a long time
for you, boy.


1077
1:11:36,96 --> 1:11:38,92
But l got you.


1078
1:11:38,92 --> 1:11:42,298
l put two Geechees in jail
in Camp Campbell, Kentucky.


1079
1:11:42,298 --> 1:11:45,635
Three in Fort Huachuca.


1080
1:11:45,635 --> 1:11:48,888
Now l've got you.


1081
1:11:48,888 --> 1:12:29,679
One less fool for the race
to be ashamed of.


1082
1:12:29,679 --> 1:12:32,849
What happened to him?


1083
1:12:32,849 --> 1:12:37,186
C.J. killed himself, sir.


1084
1:12:37,186 --> 1:12:43,443
The day after l saw him,
the MPs found him
hanging from the bars.


1085
1:12:43,443 --> 1:12:45,445
We lost our last game.


1086
1:12:45,445 --> 1:12:47,488
We just threw it.


1087
1:12:47,488 --> 1:12:50,158
We did it for C.J.


1088
1:12:50,158 --> 1:12:54,495
Captain Taylor was mad
because we ain't get to
play the Yankees.


1089
1:12:54,495 --> 1:13:4,505
Peterson was right
on that one. We needed
to protest that man.


1090
1:13:4,505 --> 1:13:6,966
And the sergeant,
what did he do?


1091
1:13:6,966 --> 1:13:8,843
Well, they broke up
the team


1092
1:13:8,843 --> 1:13:12,847
and they assigned us to this here
smoke-generating company.


1093
1:13:12,847 --> 1:13:16,517
And the sarge,
he just started acting funny.


1094
1:13:16,517 --> 1:13:19,479
He stayed drunk
all the time.


1095
1:13:19,479 --> 1:13:21,689
What time did you get in
the night he was killed?


1096
1:13:21,689 --> 1:13:24,484
Between 2120 and 9:30.


1097
1:13:24,484 --> 1:13:27,487
Me and Henson listened
to The Jack Benny show,


1098
1:13:27,487 --> 1:13:31,741
played checkers.
Who was the last man in that night?


1099
1:13:31,741 --> 1:13:34,243
Peterson and Smalls.
They had guard duty, sir.


1100
1:13:34,243 --> 1:13:36,412
[ENGlNE STARTS]


1101
1:13:36,412 --> 1:13:38,998
ls that it, captain?
Thank you, corporal.


1102
1:13:38,998 --> 1:13:48,883
Yes, sir.


1103
1:13:48,883 --> 1:13:55,932
BYRD:
Eight ball, corner pocket.


1104
1:13:55,932 --> 1:13:58,518
Whose idea was this, Charlie?
Nivens.


1105
1:13:58,518 --> 1:14:2,48
And you have to clear
the area, Jim. We're here
to question these two.


1106
1:14:2,48 --> 1:14:12,115
He's got no business in here.
Take it up with the colonel.


1107
1:14:12,115 --> 1:14:14,826
Now, this is
Captain Davenport.


1108
1:14:14,826 --> 1:14:20,331
You both understand,
you're to give the captain
your full cooperation.


1109
1:14:20,331 --> 1:14:22,458
You're a lawyer, huh?


1110
1:14:22,458 --> 1:14:25,503
l'm not here to answer
your questions, lieutenant.


1111
1:14:25,503 --> 1:14:32,51
Sit down.


1112
1:14:32,51 --> 1:14:38,99
Yes, sir.


1113
1:14:38,99 --> 1:14:42,395
When did you last see Waters?
Same night somebody killed him.


1114
1:14:42,395 --> 1:14:46,899
Course, l should've
done it myself by the way
he spoke to Wilcox and me.


1115
1:14:46,899 --> 1:14:48,943
How did he speak
to you, captain?


1116
1:14:48,943 --> 1:14:52,53
Well, he was drunk.
He said a few things
he shouldn't have.


1117
1:14:52,53 --> 1:14:56,45
l told the lieutenant not to make
the situation any worse than it was.


1118
1:14:56,45 --> 1:15:1,164
So we just left him there,
on the side of the road,
on his knees.


1119
1:15:1,164 --> 1:15:5,376
Alive.


1120
1:15:5,376 --> 1:15:7,879
Exactly what did he say?


1121
1:15:7,879 --> 1:15:11,382
He said he wasn't gonna obey
the white man's orders anymore.


1122
1:15:11,382 --> 1:15:14,719
And he starts blaming
Wilcox and me for him being black.


1123
1:15:14,719 --> 1:15:18,55
l mean, imagine that, huh?
Hell, l didn't even know the man.


1124
1:15:18,55 --> 1:15:20,766
WlLCOX:
Yeah and he said
he killed somebody too.


1125
1:15:20,766 --> 1:15:23,811
And some pretty
insulting things about us.


1126
1:15:23,811 --> 1:15:25,771
l mean, uh, white officers.


1127
1:15:25,771 --> 1:15:27,773
Did he say who?
Mention a name?


1128
1:15:27,773 --> 1:15:30,568
BYRD:
Look, the goddamn nigger
was disrespectful.


1129
1:15:30,568 --> 1:15:33,946
No way a colored soldier
speak to a white officer like that.


1130
1:15:33,946 --> 1:15:36,449
What are we doing,
wasting time on this, huh?


1131
1:15:36,449 --> 1:15:39,911
You answer him
like he wants you to, Byrd,


1132
1:15:39,911 --> 1:15:42,914
or l'll stick it to your ass
every chance l get.


1133
1:15:42,914 --> 1:15:44,207
You got that?


1134
1:15:44,207 --> 1:15:45,583
Yes, sir.


1135
1:15:45,583 --> 1:15:47,418
Captain, let me handle this.


1136
1:15:47,418 --> 1:15:53,341
Then handle it.


1137
1:15:53,341 --> 1:15:56,636
You said he was disrespectful.
ls that why you killed him?


1138
1:15:56,636 --> 1:15:59,889
l killed no one.
Sit down.


1139
1:15:59,889 --> 1:16:1,766
You hit him?
Knocked him down.


1140
1:16:1,766 --> 1:16:3,184
Shot him.
He was alive.


1141
1:16:3,184 --> 1:16:4,852
You beat him up, shot him.


1142
1:16:4,852 --> 1:16:7,98
Get out of my face before l kill you.
Like Waters?


1143
1:16:7,98 --> 1:16:9,357
No!
TAYLOR: Soldier.


1144
1:16:9,357 --> 1:16:11,817
He's trying to put it on me.
Sit down.


1145
1:16:11,817 --> 1:16:18,407
Answer his questions, lieutenant.


1146
1:16:18,407 --> 1:16:21,35
You were both coming off bivouac?
Speak up.


1147
1:16:21,35 --> 1:16:23,204
You had weapons.
But we didn't fire.


1148
1:16:23,204 --> 1:16:25,414
When did you turn them in?
Right away.


1149
1:16:25,414 --> 1:16:27,25
Nivens took our .45s
to the MPs.


1150
1:16:27,25 --> 1:16:28,459
He wanted it quiet.


1151
1:16:28,459 --> 1:16:31,754
Didn't want colored boys
to know anybody white
was involved.


1152
1:16:31,754 --> 1:16:33,881
But those weapons
cleared ballistics.


1153
1:16:33,881 --> 1:16:37,635
BYRD: Besides, we've been
short on .45 caliber ammo for,
what, six months?


1154
1:16:37,635 --> 1:16:41,138
lt's for MPs
and special-duty people only.


1155
1:16:41,138 --> 1:16:45,935
Look, nobody on that exercise
was issued any.


1156
1:16:45,935 --> 1:16:48,604
What?


1157
1:16:48,604 --> 1:16:54,277
l said, sir, nobody on the bivouac
was issued any .45 ammo.


1158
1:16:54,277 --> 1:16:56,487
l don't believe you.


1159
1:16:56,487 --> 1:16:58,3
Why wasn't l told?


1160
1:16:58,3 --> 1:17:1,534
The weapons had cleared,
the colonel felt if he involved you,


1161
1:17:1,534 --> 1:17:4,245
you'd go to Washington,
which you did anyway.


1162
1:17:4,245 --> 1:17:8,207
Sir, l just wanna say
we were not involved
with the sergeant's death.


1163
1:17:8,207 --> 1:17:9,75
Now, l'm a doctor.


1164
1:17:9,75 --> 1:17:12,336
We left that man on
the side of the road. Alive.


1165
1:17:12,336 --> 1:17:14,714
TAYLOR:
You're under arrest.
The charge is murder.


1166
1:17:14,714 --> 1:17:15,923
BYRD:
Captain--


1167
1:17:15,923 --> 1:17:20,428
TAYLOR:
You think l believe that crap?


1168
1:17:20,428 --> 1:17:22,555
Let them go.


1169
1:17:22,555 --> 1:17:23,889
What?


1170
1:17:23,889 --> 1:17:28,853
WlLCOX: Are we being charged?
DAVENPORT: Not by me.


1171
1:17:28,853 --> 1:17:34,358
What are you doing?
You've got a motive,
you've got a witness.


1172
1:17:34,358 --> 1:17:36,319
l mean, what more
do you want?


1173
1:17:36,319 --> 1:17:40,573
This is still my investigation,
Charlie.


1174
1:17:40,573 --> 1:17:43,909
We've both been had, captain.
Colonel knew this all along.


1175
1:17:43,909 --> 1:17:47,83
Been marching around in circles.
They are guilty and you know it.


1176
1:17:47,83 --> 1:17:50,41
Now, l'll back you up.
Charge them.


1177
1:17:50,41 --> 1:17:54,795
l do what the facts tell me, not you.
You don't know what a fact is.


1178
1:17:54,795 --> 1:17:57,715
l'm the lawyer.
They teach law at West Point?


1179
1:17:57,715 --> 1:18:1,761
You don't have to
be a lawyer to deal
with those two assholes.


1180
1:18:1,761 --> 1:18:5,431
And if they didn't
kill Waters, who did?


1181
1:18:5,431 --> 1:18:8,851
l don't know yet.


1182
1:18:8,851 --> 1:18:13,272
[♪♪♪]


1183
1:18:13,272 --> 1:18:22,573
[ALL SHOUTlNG lNDlSTlNCTLY]


1184
1:18:22,573 --> 1:18:28,37
What do you know
about C.J. Memphis?


1185
1:18:28,37 --> 1:18:31,207
A great ballplayer.


1186
1:18:31,207 --> 1:18:32,583
Committed suicide.


1187
1:18:32,583 --> 1:18:37,38
lt was a tragedy.


1188
1:18:37,38 --> 1:18:41,384
